ers%2C%20and%20more.%20It%20was%20the%20longest-recorded%20Senate%20floor%20speech%20in%20American%20history%2C%20and%20it%20prevented%20the%20GOP-controlled%20Senate%20from%20doing%20anything%20else%2C%20temporarily%20delaying%20the%20confirmation%20of%20some%20of%20Trump's%20nominees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBooker%20never%20left%20to%20use%20the%20restroom.%20He%20didn't%20eat%20a%20meal.%20He%20stood%20largely%20in%20the%20same%20spot%20behind%20his%20desk%20on%20the%20left%20side%20of%20the%20chamber%3B%20his%20speech%20was%20occasionally%20interrupted%20by%20a%20Democratic%20colleague%20whose%20friendly%20questions%20allowed%20him%20quick%20reprieves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20of%20Booker's%20colleagues%20have%20done%20the%20same%20in%20the%20last%2012%20years%2C%20including%20Republican%20Sens.%20Ted%20Cruz%20of%20Texas%20and%20Rand%20Paul%20of%20Kentucky%2C%20along%20with%20Democratic%20Sens.%20Jeff%20Merkley%20of%20Oregon%20and%20Chris%20Murphy%20of%20Connecticut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDelivering%20a%20speech%20like%20this%20requires%20stamina%20%E2%80%94%20and%20careful%20preparation.%20Just%20ask%20Cruz%2C%20who%20in%202013%20spoke%20for%2021%20hours%20and%2018%20minutes%20against%20the%20Affordable%20Care%20Act.%20Earlier%20that%20year%2C%20Paul%20had%20spoken%20for%20almost%2013%20hours%20in%20opposition%20to%20former%20President%20Barack%20Obama's%20nominee%20to%20be%20CIA%20director%2C%20and%20the%20Kentucky%20Republican%20offered%20Cruz%20some%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20said%2C%20No.%201%2C%20wear%20comfortable%20shoes%2C%26quot%3B%20Cruz%20recalled%20on%20Tuesday.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20he%20said%2C%20number%20two%2C%20drink%20very%20little%20water.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20delicate%20question%20%E2%80%94%20what%20if%20you%20really%20have%20to%20pee%3F%20Paul%20ended%20his%20own%202013%20speech%20by%20noting%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20are%20some%20limits%20to%20filibustering%2C%20and%20I%20am%20going%20to%20have%20to%20go%20take%20care%20of%2